quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  103,1,"By the time!"
  103,2,"Lo! Man is in a state of loss;"
  103,3,"save those who have faith and do righteous deeds, and counsel each other to hold on to truth and counsel each other to be steadfast."{1},footnotes:1:1
  104,1,"Woe to every fault-finding backbiter;"{1},footnotes:1:1
  104,2,"who amasses wealth and counts it over and again."{1},footnotes:1:1
  104,3,"He thinks that his wealth will immortalise him forever."{1},footnotes:1:1
  104,4,"Nay, he shall be thrown into the Crusher."{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  104,5,"And what do you know what the Crusher is?"
  104,6,"It is the Fire kindled by Allah,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  104,7,"the Fire that shall rise to the hearts (of criminals)."{1},footnotes:1:1
  104,8,"Verily it will close in upon them,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  104,9,"in outstretched columns."{1},footnotes:1:1
  105,1,"Have you not seen how your Lord dealt with the people of the elephants?"{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  105,2,"Did He not bring their plan to naught?"{1}{2},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2
  105,3,"And He sent against them swarms of birds"{1},footnotes:1:1
  105,4,"which smote them with stones of baked clay,"{1},footnotes:1:1
  105,5,"and made them like straw eaten up (by cattle)."{1},footnotes:1:1